3521, "(fr)Excellent job, pilot! Intelligence reports the transports arrived safely in the Gamma Draconis system. 

As a result of your outstanding service to the Alliance, I am recommending your transfer to the GTD Aquitaine, flagship of the 3rd Fleet. Should you undertake this assignment, you will serve on the front lines of our war against the Shivans, fighting to secure peace for all systems of the GTVA. 

Completing this campaign will not be easy, pilot. You must acquire mastery of the fighters, bombers, and weapons in our arsenal. You must venture into the nebula to uncover its secrets, and confront the most powerful adversary we as a civilization have ever faced. You'll work hand-in-hand with our Vasudan allies, and maybe even command one of their squadrons. If you succeed, you will have the satisfaction that you helped secure the future of humanity and our place in the cosmos. "

3522, "(fr)You escorted one of the transports safely to the Gamma Draconis system. Considering what you faced out there, that's not too bad.

Allied Intelligence has called for a formal inquiry into the loss of the other vessel you were assigned to protect. However, had they done a better job anticipating the extent of the Shivan attack, we would have been better prepared. Only a top-notch pilot could have repelled all those bombers. You did what you could, and Command will stand by you.

The road ahead will not be easy, pilot. We are fighting the most powerful adversary we as a civilization have ever faced. We must work hand-in-hand with our Vasudan allies, and if we succeed, we'll know that we helped secure the future of humanity and our place in the cosmos. "

