3785, "(fr)Welcome to the Stingrays

This is Commander Degas.  As leader of the respected 97th Stingrays here aboard the GTD Mandrill, I'm pleased to welcome you into our squadron.  The Stingrays are just one of 20 squadrons stationed aboard this vessel, which includes such notable squads as the 128th Sharks and the 84th Orcas.

We are confident that you will uphold the stringent code of honor that dictates our conduct.  Welcome aboard, pilot."

3786, "(fr)Distress Signal

Unfortunately, your stay will not be a long one.  Merely 10 minutes ago, we received a distress signal from the new Vasudan destroyer and our sister ship, the GVD Nekhbet.  The transmission follows..."

3787, "(fr)> Transmission from GVD Nekhbet
> 1058 hours, General Vasudan Military Time

<Begin transmission>

This is the GVD Nekhbet.  During a system diagnostic test, we encountered a problem with our main reactor.  The reactor malfunctioned and it caused our engines to completely shut down.  This has also rendered our beam weapons and other defensive mechanisms off-line."

3788, "(fr)<Transmission continued>

Just a few moments ago, a Shivan scouting wing encountered our disabled vessel.  Unfortunately, our minimal defenses were unable to neutralize all targets and some escaped.  We fear that they will bring reinforcements.

For now, we are running on our third backup generator that keeps our communications system operational.  We need assistance.  GTVA Command, please respond..."

3789, "(fr)Pilot, you are that response.  This is a situation that could turn critical without prompt action.  Therefore, we are dispatching Alpha and Beta Wings of the Stingrays to assist and defend the Nekhbet.

Suit up.  Mission briefing commences in five minutes."

3790, "(fr)At roughly 1100 hours, the $g GTD $g Mandrill received a distress call from the newly commissioned Hatshepsut destroyer, the $g GVD $g Nekhbet.  A reactor malfunction has rendered the Nekhbet defenseless and immobile.  It is also believed that the Shivans now know of the Nekhbet's status."

3791, "(fr)The Vasudans are unable to get a reinforcement fleet into the area in time.  Therefore, we are dispatching $g Alpha and $g Beta $g Wings to secure the area around the Nekhbet and defend it from any and all hostiles."

3792, "(fr)We will also send in an Argo transport, designated $g Omega, to dock with the Nekhbet and attempt to repair its reactor.  The crew of the Omega will first try to restore the ship's defensive array and then its engines."

3793, "(fr)Lastly, we have ordered the $g GTCv $g Echelon to be on standby elsewhere in the Vega System.  This is all we can do until Vasudan reinforcements arrive."

3794, "(fr)In the event of any unseen problems that threaten the Nekhbet, you are to await further orders from Terran Command.  We anticipate a Shivan offensive, but the size and power of their attack is unknown."

3795, "(fr)The 8,100 Vasudans aboard the Nekhbet are counting on you, pilot.  Do not let them down.  Good luck.  Commander Degas, out."

3796, "(fr)As Commander of the Stingrays, I officially annul all of your designations and awards.  Your membership with the Stingrays has been terminated, if not your entire career.  Desertion from any scenario without the consent of your commanding officer is punishable by a court martial.

This behavior is intolerable, pilot.  I am ashamed that I brought you aboard our squadron in the first place.  In our quest to become the most respected squadron aboard the GTD Mandrill, we have no use for cowards like you."

