4163, "(fr)This is Admiral Petrach, Commanding officer of the GTD Aquitaine.  To all the new pilots arriving onboard the Aquitaine, welcome.

The Aquitaine was the first of the Hecate destroyers, brought into service shortly before the Second Great War.  The Aquitaine bore the brunt of the fighting against the Shivans in the Gamma Draconis and Capella systems.  We're part of history here, pilot."

4164, "(fr)Two years have passed since the collapsing of the Jump nodes leading to Capella.  Two years without sight nor sound of the Shivans.  If we have learned anything from our past experiences, it is that we cannot take for granted the recent peace we have enjoyed.  At any time, we could be thrust back into the chaos of war."

4165, "(fr)As you probably already know, the scientists who discovered the Knossos portal which caused the Shivan incursion into our space for the second time have begun work on a portal between Delta Serpentis and Sol.  The Aquitaine's objective is to oversee construction and neutralize any threat."

4166, "(fr)The biggest source of danger comes from the newly resurrected Hammer of Light.  If you have studied the history of the GTVA, you will know that the Hammer of Light is a Vasudan splinter group, commited to acts of terrorism against the GTVA.

HOL forces have been seen in several key locations in Delta Serpentis, therefore we will have to be on the lookout.

Several errant transmissions have been detected in systems throughtout GTVA space, thus we believe the HOL is amassing for a strike against us."

4167, "(fr)At 1730 hrs yesterday, several strange readings were recorded by a science vessel on the edge of the Ross 128 system.  The readings were not wholly conclusive, but indicate some kind of activity in the system.

Command thinks that this could be an HOL staging area, so we are sending the Aquiatine to deal with the renegades."

4168, "(fr)The Aquitaine will arrive in system within the hour.   Alpha Wing will recon the area and, if necessary, eliminate hostile vessels.  We will not commit the Aquitaine unless it is absolutely imperative."

4169, "(fr)Your squadron and the Aquitaine were victorious.  Your victory has boosted the morale of servicemen and women throughout Terran-Vasudan space.  You and your squad are to be commended."

4170, "(fr)Your incompetence has left the lives of millions in jeopardy, pilot.  You are stripped of all rank and privileges until further notice.  You will be transferred to the freighter depot at Antares, where you can spend your remaining days piloting a Triton."

4171, "(fr)The cowardly way in which you left the battlefield has left the entire future of Terran-Vasudan space in jeopardy."

4172, "(fr)Unfortunately, the fate of our civilizations now hangs in the balance.  Scientists have detected dozens of these devices within the Ross 128 system, along with more within Ikeya and Laramis.  The Third Shivan invasion is apparently upon us, a war which we have little chance of winning.  The Hammer of Light pales in significance when compared with this new threat. "

