4196, "(fr)The Story So Far

The year is 2374. Seven years have passed since the destruction of Capella and the end of the second Great War. Morale is high as the Galactic Terran-Vasudan Alliance completes its most expensive and ambitious project to date: The Knossos Project."

4197, "(fr)It appears that no one can challenge the superiority of the GTVA.  Admiral Bosch's Neo Terran Front has been reduced to warring groups of rag-tag pirates.  The Shivans have been stranded in Capella and haven't been heard from since the final days of the Second Great War.  

However, unbeknownst to the Alliance, an ancient foe waits in the shadows for the time to strike back on the victors of a conflict that ended a generation ago."

4198, "(fr)You are a pilot on the GTD Ithica. A top pilot of the graduating class of 2373 at the academy, you are assigned to the 119th Blue Devils Squadron.  A child of the lost generation, you prepare to fight for a planet you have only heard of in story books and of beauty that you can only dream of."

4199, "(fr)* GTD Ithica - 08-25-2374 - Delta Serpentis *

Welcome Aboard from Admiral Renniger

I'd like to extend a warm welcome to the new pilots assigned to the 132nd Argonauts and the 119th Blue Devils squadrons. I believe you'll find your new ship- and squad-mates to be very helpful and courteous."

4200, "(fr)GTD Ithica

The GTD Ithica, a Hecate-class destroyer,  has served the Galactic Terran-Vasudan Alliance for over two years.  Commissioned in 2372, the Ithica is home to four fighter squadrons, two companies of Terran Marines, and ten thousand crew members. The Ithica has played an important role in the GTVA fleet, partcipating in such anti-pirate operations as Operation Skyhook and Operation Overlord. Serve the Ithica well, she's a fine ship.

From here, I will turn this briefing over to your new squadron leaders."

4201, "(fr)119th Blue Devils

Welcome to the 119th, pilot.  I'm Lt. Cmdr. Taubach, squadron leader of the Blue Devils.

The Blue Devils are a multi-role squadron.  We are called upon to do a multitude of tasks and Command expects us to do each task to the best of our ability, whether it be a patrol, an escort, or a strike. I trust that you will make a fine addition to our proud squadron."

4202, "(fr)Knossos Project

As you know, the Terra Knossos is nearing completion in the Delta Serpentis system.  Dr. Hargrove and her staff are working around the clock to prepare for the activation of the device that is scheduled to occur in two weeks.  

While the GTD Ithica is dispatched to Beta Aquilae to oversee the settling of the Vasudan Laborers Union and the Akheton Corporation's labor dispute, the 119th will be left behind in Delta Serpentis to safeguard the completion of the Terra Knossos. Briefing follows."

4203, "(fr)Construction has just been completed on a GTI Arcadia station near $f Knossos $f Point in the Delta Serpentis system."

4204, "(fr)The delivery of the station's fighter complement has been delayed, leaving the station undefended.  While the Ithica heads toward the Beta Aquilae system, the 119th and the 43rd squadrons will be assigned to protect the station."

4205, "(fr)Station activity has been high in the last few weeks due to the scheduled test of the $f Terra $f Knossos in sixteen days.  Expect a number of transports to be in the area between the station and the Knossos."

4206, "(fr)Command fears that increased pirate activity in the Ross 128 system may carry over to the Delta Serpentis system.  Any attack on the station is very likely to come from the nearby jump node to Ross 128."

4207, "(fr)You may notice Dr. Hargrove and her staff working at the Terra Knossos portal.  You are not to interfere with her work and are to keep a distance of ten thousand meters from the Von Braun at all times. "

4208, "(fr)Fifteen minutes after you launch, the GTD Calypso will relieve your patrol and deliver the Station's fighter complement.

"

4209, "(fr)Do not underestimate the importance of this mission, pilot.  Seven years of work and trillions of credits have been poured into the Knossos Project.  It all comes down to this patrol on whether or not we succeed in returning to our home planet.  Good luck, pilot.  Dismissed.

"

4210, "(fr)Thanks to your efforts, Knossos station survived the pirate attack and the project is still on schedule for its testing sequence.  Commander Ordover, magistrate of the station, commends you for your fine work."

4211, "(fr)The loss of the station will clear a path to future attacks on the Terra Knossos and ultimatly delay our return home.  This kind of performance is not acceptable, pilot.  You have been confined to quarters until a proper hearing can take place."

4212, "(fr)The desertion of your post opened up Knossos Station for a massive pirate attack.  The station didn't stand a chance.  Not only did we lose the station, but the pirates managed to land a number of heavy torpedo hits on the Von Braun, killing Dr. Hargrove and many members of her staff.  You have been confined to quarters pending a court martial hearing.  "

4213, "(fr)GTVA officials have tracked the actual science cruiser that was to be used by Dr. Nelson and her staff to the Ross 128 system.  Approximately twelve hours before the arrival of GTVA investigation forces, the Faustus carrying her was destroyed by pirate insurgents.  It is not believed her death will delay the completion date of the Terra Knossos and its subsequent tests."

4214, "(fr)Our squadron has been reassigned to Knossos Station until the Ithica returns to Delta Serpentis. All pilots will find their temporary room assignments on the squadron message board at 1400 hours.  Dismissed."

